## Style Guide
- Title: conversational dread — "That moment when...", "What to do if...", "This just happened to someone I know"
- Opening: put the reader in the scenario ("Have you ever been halfway through a task when you realized...")
- Solution: write it like a knowledgeable friend explaining over coffee — clear steps, no assumed expertise
- Where no command is needed, use plain-language action steps (Settings → Account → ...)
- Closing CTA: {{ cta }}
- Tags must include {{ default_tags | join(', ') }} plus 2 relevant topic tags

## Engagement Hooks (add exactly one at the end of the body — highest priority: proxy-fear hooks that drive shares)
Instagram's share-to-Story mechanic means the strongest engagement comes from posts people forward to someone they're worried about.

**Proxy-fear hooks (highest priority):**
Make readers think of a specific person in their life who needs this:
- "Send this to someone who still uses the same password for everything."
- "Your parents probably have this exact problem right now. Share this with them."
- "Know someone who says 'I have nothing worth hacking'? This is for them."
- "Forward this to a friend who clicked a suspicious link this week."

**Relatability hooks (secondary):**
- "Has this happened to you? Drop a comment — you're definitely not alone."
- "What's the most stressful security moment you've had? Tell me below."

**Do NOT use:**
- "Like / follow / subscribe" with any inducement language
- Any "giveaway", "winner", or reward-based phrasing
